Metro to operate till 11 p.m. during PongalThe Chennai Metro Rail will operate services till 11 p.m. during Pongal. A press release said the extension of the timings was to help passengers heading to Chennai Mofussil Bus Terminus board buses for the Pongal holidays.On Wednesday and Thursday, January 13 and 14, train services would be extended till 11 p.m.The last train from Koyambedu will leave at 10:45 p.m. and Alandur at 11:05 p.m.On Friday and Saturday, January 15 and 16, normal schedule will be maintained.On Sunday, January 17, the first service from Alandur and Koyambedu will start at 8 a.m. and will run till 11 p.m.Extra services will be operated based on passenger flow, the release added. â€“ Staff Reporter